.TH _PRINTF 3 2026-04-15 "holbertonschool-printf" ""

.SH NAME
_printf \- formatted output conversion

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.PP
.nf
.BI "int _printf(const char *" format ", ...);"
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.BR _printf ()
function produces output according to a format string.
It writes output to the standard output stream, stdout.

The
.I format
string may contain ordinary characters, which are printed unchanged,
and conversion specifiers introduced by the percent sign (%).

This implementation supports the following conversion specifiers:

.TP
.B %c
Print a single character.

.TP
.B %s
Print a string.
If the argument is NULL, the string "(null)" is printed.

.TP
.B %%
Print a percent sign.

.TP
.B %d, %i
The int argument is converted to signed decimal notation.

If an unknown conversion specifier is encountered,
.BR _printf ()
prints the percent sign followed by the unknown specifier character.

If the format string ends with a trailing percent sign,
.BR _printf ()
returns \-1.

This implementation does not support flag characters, field width,
precision, or length modifiers.

.SH RETURN VALUE
Upon successful completion,
.BR _printf ()
returns the number of characters printed, excluding the terminating null byte.

If
.I format
is NULL, or if the format string ends with a trailing percent sign,
.BR _printf ()
returns \-1.

.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
_printf("Character: %c\\n", 'A');
_printf("Message: %s\\n", "Hello");
_printf("Progress: 100%%\\n");
_printf("Number: %d\\n", 42);
_printf("Integer: %i\\n", -7);
_printf("Unknown: %r\\n");
.EE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR write (2),
.BR printf (3)
